The paper proposes a new algorithm for resource allocation in cloud computing, which involves optimization techniques such as genetic algorithm and multi-agent optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves artificial intelligence techniques such as decentralized-based MAO algorithm, which suggests the possibility of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The use of optimization techniques also suggests the possibility of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the optimization of resource utilization and bandwidth cost, which suggests the possibility of cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
